sentences.sContent: Hirst said the tooth, believed to be a child's incisor, may have come from incidents he had at school.
sentences.sContent_eng: Hirst said the tooth, believed to be a child's incisor, may have come from incidents he had at school.
sentences.sCn: 赫斯特说，据信是儿童门牙的这个牙齿，可能来自于他在学校念书时所发生的一些事。

sentences.sContent: In the TEL condition, the cue was presented alone, and participants made two guesses (such as canine, incisor) before the correct target "molar" was shown.

sentences.sCn: 而在试误学习中，线索单独呈现，在目标词“臼齿”呈现之前，被试可以猜测两次（例如，犬齿，或者门牙）。
